race.comment: DELTASON (9) was out-classed in the Max Simmonds first-up but drops right back in grade today. He'll be better for that performance and this looks to set up very well for him. Drawn well today and can land the knockout blow. FLAGSHIP (4) hasn't been far away in recent races and is knocking on the door of another win. He was only 1.2L away in stronger company last time out when favourite and the rating he put up there stacks up in this field. Can put his best foot forward now and return to winning ways. DE GRANDHOMME (3) missed first-up on a Heavy deck but went to Geraldton last start where he won easily in a CL2. He rates well on that effort and still has some upside. Drawn ideally and can bring up back-to-back wins without surprising. CRYPTIC JOY (8) was just too far back at Ascot last start and can improve back in grade and with that run under his belt. KING'S DRAMA (6) is racing in good order and is worth including.
